   density and incident angle parameters were analyzed and calibrated, and
   the local incident angle was used as a substitute for the satellite
   incident angle to improve the snow depth estimation. From the results,
   the coherence images showed that a high degree of coherence can be found
   for dry snow, and, apart from the effect of snow, land use/cover change
